OOP:Object Oriented Programming

1)Object:Any entity which has own state 
and behaviour
ex:Pen,paper etc...

2)class:collection of objects
ex:Human body

3)abstraction:Hiding internal details and 
showing functionalities

4)Encapsulation:Wrapping up of data or 
binding of data
ex:capsule

5)Inheritance:When one object acquire all
the properties and behaviour of parent class
ex:father-son

6)Polymorphism:Many ways to perform anything
ex:
1)Method Overloading
2)Method Overriding


